towards Black's kingside. The next step in the plan is to double the rooks on
the e-line, play Bf4 and start attacking. As you can see in the game, by
bringing the queen to h4, White isn't in a hurry to play Ng5 and create a
temporary attack. He is bulding his attack slowly by activating all of his
pieces.} h6 18. Rfe1 {Please also notice that White is creating positional
threats. Right now, he is threatening a pawn sacrifice with e6 in order to cut
Black's position into two.} Qe6 19. Re3 a5 20. Rae1 a4 21. Bf4 $5 {
He is creating a direct threat to weaken Black's kingside pawn formation.} (21.
